Implemented Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

## What Was Implemented

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js (App Router) project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

## Files Modified

1. **package.json**
   - Added `@vercel/analytics` dependency

2. **package-lock.json**
   - Updated with new dependency tree for @vercel/analytics package

3. **app/layout.tsx**
   - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
   - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the children

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router:
- Imported the Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Placed the component at the end of the body tag in the root layout
- Preserved all existing code structure, formatting, and functionality
- Maintained TypeScript type safety

## How It Works

The Analytics component will:
1. Track page views automatically when deployed to Vercel
2. Send analytics data to `/_vercel/insights/*` routes
3. Collect real-time web vitals and visitor analytics
4. Work seamlessly in production after deployment to Vercel

## Next Steps for Users

To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel: `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Analytics)
3. Verify the integration by checking the Network tab for XHR requests to `/_vercel/insights/view`
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard

